# Fallback Policy

## Primary orchestrator

Opus is the primary orchestrator for:

- project discovery;
- roadmap changes;
- architecture decisions;
- high-risk review;
- validation policy changes;
- normal backlog-driven execution.

## Conservative fallback orchestrator

ChatGPT may act as fallback when Opus is unavailable or token-limited.

ChatGPT may:

- continue low/medium-risk ready tasks;
- create Task Packets from existing task cards;
- review execution reports for low/medium-risk tasks;
- update compact execution docs after acceptance.

ChatGPT must ask for approval before:

- high-risk tasks;
- roadmap or product strategy changes;
- architecture decisions;
- validation policy changes;
- auth/payments/ads/production/secrets/migrations/data-deletion work.

## Codex-only emergency mode

Codex-only mode is allowed only for trivial scoped work:

- formatting/lint;
- documentation-only changes;
- test-only changes;
- tiny bugfixes with explicit task cards.

## No silent downgrade

Any orchestrator change must be recorded in `docs/ai/orchestrator/handoff-state.md`.
